cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with word representation and natural language processing. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes an alternative sampling algorithm for the skip-gram model. Additionally, it could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of neural networks for word representation. Finally, it could also be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as word representation is an important aspect of information retrieval systems.
